com.mobius.vdrapi
Class ViewDirectSeverityLevel

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.mobius.vdrapi.ViewDirectSeverityLevel
public final class ViewDirectSeverityLevel
extends Object

This class defines the severity of events that can occur during the execution of API functions, and is used to indicate the level of trace output. There are five possible values that you can set, ranging in severity level from "OK" to "Disaster".

It is important to be aware that an "OK" setting will generate many more server messages than "Disaster", and may result in decreased server performance.

Field Detail

SL_DISASTER

public static final ViewDirectSeverityLevel SL_DISASTER
Sets the SeverityLevel value to "disaster". This setting logs the fewest number of server messages, namely only those messages indicating fatal errors caused by internal logic problems, and is the recommended setting for optimal system performance.

SL_ERROR

public static final ViewDirectSeverityLevel SL_ERROR
Sets the SeverityLevel value to "error". This setting logs all fatal error and disaster messages.

SL_EXCEPTION

public static final ViewDirectSeverityLevel SL_EXCEPTION
Sets the SeverityLevel value to "exception". This setting logs all exceptions (recoverable errors), as well as all error and disaster messages.

SL_OK

public static final ViewDirectSeverityLevel SL_OK
Sets the SeverityLevel value to "OK". This setting logs the greatest number of server messages, including all informational, warning, exception, error, and disaster messages.

SL_WARNING

public static final ViewDirectSeverityLevel SL_WARNING
Sets the SeverityLevel value to "warning". This setting logs all warning, exception, error, and disaster messages.
